Any free elective can go here. Recommended: MU161. Majors must demonstrate piano proficiency as part of the mid-point evaluation. Any piano classes needed before the piano proficiency examination will count as free electives. Completion of MU263 with a C- or better represents fulfillment of the piano proficiency examination.

One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, B4, Upper-Division B, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, D2, D2, Upper-Division D, E, and GE Electives (8). Upper-Division B, Upper-Division C, and Upper-Division D should be taken only after junior standing is reached (90 units). Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: Upper-Division B, C1, Upper-Division C, D1, Upper-Division D, or E.
